cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically video event detection, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also extensively discusses deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with multimedia data, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. The paper also discusses the reorganization of the ImageNet hierarchy, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses fusion with other modalities, which could place it in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
